Christopher Panayiotou and two others are on trial for orchestrating the kidnap and murder of Jayde Panayiotou two years ago. CAPE TOWN - The Port Elizabeth High Court is considering the admissibility of a video recording in which Christopher Panayiotou allegedly implicates himself in his wife's murder.The businessman and two others are on trial for orchestrating Jayde Panayiotou s kidnapping and murder two years ago. Her body was found on the outskirts of Uitenhage shortly after she had gone missing. Defence Advocate Terry Price has questioned investigating officer Kanna Swanepoel about how he got permission to set up a sting operation, during which the accused met his former employee Luthando Siyoni at a filling station.Police facilitated calls between Panayiotou and Siyoni shortly after Jayde's body was discovered and Siyoni was taken into custody.Swanepoel has testified when this turned out to be fruitless, a plan was put in place for the two men to meet in person.The officer has told the court he would not have continued without permission from the office of the director of public prosecutions, but he could also not say for certain whether he made the call or instructed another officer to place the call.(Edited by Winnie Theletsane)